menu "Blob Detection"

config BLOB_THRESHOLD_PCT
    int "Foreground threshold (% of mean brightness)"
    default 65
    range 1 99
    help
        A pixel is treated as foreground (insect) if its brightness is below
        this percentage of the image mean brightness.

        threshold = mean_brightness * BLOB_THRESHOLD_PCT / 100

        Lower values → only very dark pixels detected (fewer false positives,
        may miss faint insects).
        Higher values → more pixels detected (catches faint insects, more noise).

        Scaling relative to mean makes this robust across different exposures:
        a dark image (mean=80) gives threshold=52; a bright image (mean=200)
        gives threshold=130 — both correctly isolate objects that are
        significantly darker than the background.

config BLOB_MIN_W
    int "Minimum blob width (pixels)"
    default 8
    range 1 320
    help
        Blobs narrower than this are discarded as noise.

config BLOB_MIN_H
    int "Minimum blob height (pixels)"
    default 8
    range 1 320
    help
        Blobs shorter than this are discarded as noise.

config BLOB_GAP_ROWS
    int "Vertical gap tolerance (rows)"
    default 4
    range 0 32
    help
        Number of background rows that can appear inside a blob before it is
        split into two separate blobs. Useful for insects with a lighter band
        across their body.

config BLOB_GAP_COLS
    int "Horizontal gap tolerance (pixels)"
    default 8
    range 0 64
    help
        Number of background pixels that can appear between two dark runs on
        the same row before they are treated as separate blobs.

endmenu
